http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Two-arrested-on-burglary-charge/article13986105.ece

The Steel Plant police arrested two persons on charge of committing burglary and recovered about 212 gm of gold ornaments from them on Wednesday.The arrested were identified as Pappu Kanaka Raju and Neeli Raj Deep.The accused allegedly burgled the house of a steel plant officer in Ukkunagaram Township a few weeks ago.On Wednesday, they tried to sell the gold at a shop in Gajuwaka. Inspector K. Durga Prasad noticed that they were suspiciously moving outside the gold shop and on questioning they spilled the beans, said ACP (South division) G.B.R. Madhusudan Babu.